<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Dear Chair</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by the Welsh Language Commissioner [FBB0042]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Welsh Language Commissioner welcomes the opportunity to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">provide evidence to the Culture, Media and Sport Committee’s inquiry into the Future of the BBC.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The principal aim of the Commissioner is to promote and facilitate the use of Welsh. This entails raising awareness of the official status of the Welsh language in Wales and imposing standards on organisations. This, in turn, will lead to the establishment of rights for Welsh speakers. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Two principles underpin the Commissioner's work: </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In Wales, the Welsh language should be treated no less favourably than the English language; </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Persons in Wales should be able to live their lives through the medium of the Welsh language if they choose to do so. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In due course, secondary legislation will introduce new powers allowing the setting and imposing of standards on organizations. Until then, the Commissioner will continue to inspect statutory Welsh language schemes through the powers inherited under the Welsh Language Act 1993.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The role of the Commissioner was created by the Welsh Language (Wales) Measure 2011. The Commissioner may investigate failure to implement a language scheme; interference with the freedom to use Welsh in Wales and, in future, complaints regarding the failure of organizations to meet standards. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">One of the Commissioner's priorities is to scrutinise Welsh language policy developments, acting as an independent advocate on behalf of Welsh speakers in Wales. This evidence is provided to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Culture, Media and Sport Committee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in that capacity.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Commissioner’s comments, and the issues which the Committee may wish to address, may be summarised as follows:-</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Welsh speakers require a comprehensive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">broadcasting</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> service of high quality in their own language.</span><span style="color:#222222; font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">As</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a public broadcaster</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in Wales</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">BBC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">has a particular duty</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">towards the Welsh language</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and has</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">an important role to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">play</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">its</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">future</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">To</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">license fee payers who</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">speak</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Welsh</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">who wish to live</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">their lives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">through the medium of Welsh</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">it is important that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">quality media</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">available to them</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in the language of their choice</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">BBC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’ </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">long tradition</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">broadcasting</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in Welsh</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is indicative of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the fact</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that it takes its duties</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">seriously. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The BBC’s continued commitment to Welsh medium media should remain central to the BBC’s public purposes, as set out in its Royal Charter.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In October 2010 the Secretary of State for Culture, Olympics, Media and Sport announced proposals to remove the statutory provisions that increased S4C’s annual funding, in line with inflation. The Secretary of State and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">BBC Trust also agreed a revised licence fee settlement for the BBC for the period until March 2017. As part of the revised settlement, the BBC Trust agreed to provide the majority of S4C’s public funding from April 2013 and to do so via a new partnership with the S4C Authority. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">This partnership between S4C as an independent television channel and the BBC Trust is of major importance in increasing and maintaining the status of the Welsh language.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The BBC’s Royal Charter expires on 31 December 2016 and funding beyond this date (to the end of 2016-17 financial year) to S4C will be dependent upon the granting of a new Royal Charter.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Whilst the BBC Trust is ultimately responsible for the stewardship of the licence fee and for ensuring value for money, the joint objective of the BBC Trust and the S4C Authority should be to ensure that the largest possible proportion of the licence fee </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">spent on providing programmes and services </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">of quality </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">in Welsh beyond </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">the end of 2016-17 financial year</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The status of the S4C Authority as an independent statutory corporation should not be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">adversely </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">affected </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">or undermined </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by the granting of a new Royal Charter to the BBC.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> S4C should retain its editorial and managerial independence from the BBC as agreed in the Operating Agreement signed by the BBC Trust and the S4C Authority in January 2013.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">At present, the BBC is under a statutory duty to provide the S4C Authority (free of charge) with sufficient television programmes in Welsh to occupy not less than 10 hours transmission time per week</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">This statutory arrangement should remain unchanged as part of the granting of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">any new</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Royal Charter</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Thank you once again for the opportunity to contribute to this inquiry. I look forward to continuing to work closely with the Culture, Media and Sport Committee.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>